#: src/tutorial.md:1
msgid "Tutorial"
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:3
msgid ""
"In this tutorial we will wrap a version of [the guessing game from The Rust "
"Book](https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch02-00-guessing-game-tutorial.html) to "
"run in Python using pyo3."
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:7
msgid "Create a new Rust project"
msgstr "建立新的 Rust 專案"

#: src/tutorial.md:9
msgid ""
"First, create a new Rust library project using `cargo new --lib --edition "
"2021 guessing-game`. This will create a directory with the following "
"structure."
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:19
msgid ""
"Edit `Cargo.toml` to configure the project and module name, and add the "
"dependencies (`rand` and `pyo3`). Configure `pyo3` with additional features "
"to make an extension module compatible with multiple Python versions using "
"the stable ABI (`abi3`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:24
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[package]\n"
"name = \"guessing-game\"\n"
"version = \"0.1.0\"\n"
"edition = \"2021\"\n"
"\n"
"[lib]\n"
"name = \"guessing_game\"\n"
"# \"cdylib\" is necessary to produce a shared library for Python to import "
"from.\n"
"crate-type = [\"cdylib\"]\n"
"\n"
"[dependencies]\n"
"rand = \"0.8.4\"\n"
"\n"
"[dependencies.pyo3]\n"
"version = \"0.18.0\"\n"
"# \"abi3-py37\" tells pyo3 (and maturin) to build using the stable ABI with "
"minimum Python version 3.7\n"
"features = [\"abi3-py37\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:44
msgid ""
"Add a `pyproject.toml` to configure [PEP 518](https://peps.python.org/"
"pep-0518/) build system requirements and enable the `extension-module` "
"feature of pyo3."
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:47
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[build-system]\n"
"requires = [\"maturin>=0.14,<0.15\"]\n"
"build-backend = \"maturin\"\n"
"\n"
"[tool.maturin]\n"
"# \"extension-module\" tells pyo3 we want to build an extension module "
"(skips linking against libpython.so)\n"
"features = [\"pyo3/extension-module\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:57
msgid "Use `maturin new`"
msgstr "使用 `maturin new`"

#: src/tutorial.md:59
msgid ""
"New projects can also be quickly created using the `maturin new` command:"
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:78
msgid ""
"The above process can be achieved by running `maturin new -b pyo3 "
"guessing_game` then edit `Cargo.toml` to add `abi3-py37` feature."
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:81
msgid "Install and configure maturin (in a virtual environment)"
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:83
msgid ""
"Create a virtual environment and install maturin. Note maturin has minimal "
"dependencies!"
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:95
msgid ""
"maturin is configured in `pyproject.toml` as introduced by [PEP 518](https://"
"www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0518/).  This file lives in the root of your "
"project tree:"
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:107
msgid ""
"Configuration in this file is quite simple for most projects. You just need "
"to indicate maturin as a requirement (and restrict the version) and as the "
"build-backend (Python supports a number of build-backends since [PEP 517]"
"(https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0517/))."
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:112
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[build-system]\n"
"requires = [\"maturin>=0.14,<0.15\"]\n"
"build-backend = \"maturin\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:118
msgid ""
"Various other tools may also be configured in `pyproject.toml` and the "
"Python community seems to be consolidating declarative configuration in this "
"file."
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:121
msgid "Program the guessing game in Rust"
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:123
msgid ""
"When you create a `lib` project with `cargo new` it creates a file `src/lib."
"rs` with some default code. Edit that file and replace the default code with "
"the code below. As mentioned, we will implement a slightly modified version "
"of [the guessing game from The Rust Book](https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/"
"ch02-00-guessing-game-tutorial.html). Instead of implementing as a `bin` "
"crate, we're using a `lib` and will expose the main logic as a Python "
"function."
msgstr ""

